snippet.textDisplay: I have bipolar disorder type five which literally makes me share personality with Eeyore every day. I have deep depressions for at least one week a month and three or four "manic" phases per year that last for three or four days. These are what most people would call really good days. Type five is quite unusual and is totally unpredictible. I go from normal to free falling into depression within ten minutes and without any warning or even reason. But life has to go on, so when the depression is over I gather the pieces and move on. It's been so for half my life, i'm 52, and it has become a strange lifestyle, almost "normal". I really like your videos, I have a black cat that always comes when he hear Sylvester. He sits down beside me and watches closely.
